   `csv.reader`. Python's `csv.writer` (default `excel` dialect) is not a
   source of row-injection risk here regardless of the field content.

3. Verified, no issue found — Content-Type/Content-Disposition. Response
   sets `media_type="text/csv"` and a static, non-user-influenced
   `Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="litlist_export.csv"`.
