differing only in `source`), and a separate, additional describe block
("re-entrancy: a single instance never commits a second decision" /
StackScreen's dedicated re-entrancy + isDecisionPending tests) now
explicitly covers the single-instance-multiple-attempts case, which the
old tests never actually exercised (the guard didn't exist yet, so nothing
